Legs densely setose, long, in male crassate and longer (
Fig. 1A
), prefemora only faintly bulging laterad; all postfemora, tibiae and tarsi typically with sphaerotrichomes ventrally.

Gonopod (
Fig. 4A
) exomere (
ex
) strongly subgeniculate at about distal ¼ and densely spinulate apically, with a strong tooth (
d
) proximal to geniculation; endomere (
en
) with a large hairy pulvillus (
pu
) at base of a slender, simple, apically curved rod (
r
) which is about half as long as 
ex
.
